What kind of insurance is it appropriate for me?
The insurance of a car which protects drivers in the event of an accident represents a significant expenditure which depends on various factors such as age, condition, sex, driving licence holding, type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing suitable car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insurance company.
This commitment takes the form of an insurance contract which provides that the insurance undertaking shall receive an agreed insurance amount of a certain amount for the purpose of taking care of the payment of damages in the event of an insurance event.
The insurance price shall be determined in the light of the various factors such as age, status, sex, length of driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the more likely the accident occurs, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both persons over 25 years of age and women must pay less insurance, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their being cautious.
In the same way, on the basis of the checks, insurance companies concluded that persons living in marriage had fewer accidents than free drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will have an impact on the frequency of driving, and thus on the likelihood that it will have an accident.
The frequency of driving increases the probability.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the insurance price.
Therefore, the driver must examine the situation well in order to choose the insurance best suited to his insurance profile.
We will show here the most important variable for the selection of a type of insurance which, apart from meeting the type of insurer, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face various disadvantages, such as a lack of driving experience and a short hold of a driving licence when they want to negotiate insurance at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are even cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all insurance risks in order to obtain insurance coverage of all risks, but at a more acceptable price.
This type of contract would provide for the participation of the client in the payment of the insurance event.
"Part of the remuneration of the insurance event provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the insurance price which will be higher, the lower the participation would be," explains Luis Noguera, the head of First Europe in Spain, an insurance intermediary on the Internet.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants in the operation by ensuring that the client is able to cope with the damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and the loss of a vehicle.
It's a recommendation.
If you are under twenty-five years old, try to be careful and avoid accidents as far as possible, because it will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate of the insurance company.
On the contrary, the malus is an increase in the above-mentioned basic rate.
"The bonus and the malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," Noguera explains.
After crossing the border for twenty-five years, it makes it easier for drivers to arrange insurance, as the client risk index decreases, thanks to acquired experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to negotiate insurance against all risks with a discount.
"Young people usually cannot take advantage of the experience gained in advance at the time of the accident and not in driving," the director of the European society in Spain assures us that most accidents occur in the second year of management, when "the fear of the new one" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks if, of course, his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered to be the lowest risk index clientele and thus their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all insurance risks (which could amount to EUR 300) or high premium, insurance extended to other operators, starting with the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their management is calmer and their purchasing capacity is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," says Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to provide insurance against all insurance risks (of which EUR 150) or insurance extended to other operators if a high bonus has been achieved.
It should be said that car insurance is important not only because it protects drivers in the event of an accident, but also because it is a significant expense, which is a good reason to properly explore insurance options that would suit us most in view of our personal situation.
